In the first move, I face a black e6, which means I'm probably going against the French defense, a break from the Sicilian Defense games that I've played and encountered. I'm hoping for a Rubenstein variation as the best case scenario, as white will have a great space advantage to work with.

Today's game features a player that plays regularly in blitz. In the first move, I face a black e6, which means I'm probably going against the French defense, a break from the Sicilian Defense games that I've played and encountered. I'm hoping for a Rubenstein variation as the best case scenario, as white will have a great space advantage to work with.
